This paper focuses on compressing convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves tensor factorization, which is a mathematical technique, indicating that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
